], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2020-03-30T09:56:57Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-09T13:11:01Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Either I couldn't find it, or at the moment there doesn't seem to be a way to query for datalad configuration parameters via the CLI?\r\n\r\nE.g. I have a small bash script that installs plugins to the user's plugin dir. To resolve the dir I'm currently doing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nget_plugin_dir() {\r\n    python3 -c \"from datalad import cfg; print(cfg.obtain('datalad.locations.user-plugins'), end='')\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nDATALAD_PLUGIN_DIR=$(get_plugin_dir)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be ideal to have something like\r\n\r\n```\r\ndatalad cfg query datalad.locations.user-plugins\r\n```\r\n\r\n`datalad wtf` is somewhat helpful here, but it only prints config params which are actually set.", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4359/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https: